   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <hazardstatement type="caution" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">REDUNDANCY LOST</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">If the manual bypass is in position 2 it is not possible
for the system to automatically switch to the static switch or bypass
if the supply from the inverter is lost.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The load is directly supplied
from the inverter. The manual bypass switch is bypassing the static
switch. The system will stay in inverter output mode until the position
of the manual bypass switch manually changes to another. No automatic
transfer is possible from this mode.</p>
         <p id="TheManualBypassSwitchShouldOnlyBeUs-01D894D3" class="- topic/p ">The manual bypass
switch should only be used for service and only for a limited period
of time.</p>
